title: 4 Rare 80s Albums [Part 144] Power Pop, New Wave, Indie Rock
description:
I am pretty sure you guys are ready to dig out some more obscure, overlooked and forgotten bands. 

On vol. 144 we have the cool power pop lp from the lads. it's an essential for anyone who is just obsessed with power pop and Mod Revival. 

Then we have a very interesting indie rock record from Swing Set. The songs all have a shimmering beauty to them that makes this album oddly attractive. 

We'll listen to the Canadian band, Jenson Interceptor and their ultra rare "Pat Benatarish" record, Cosmetics.  

Lastly check out Jimmy and the Boys and their 1981 record, Teddy Boys Picnic. Back then this was my introduction to Ignatius Jones and his Aussie new wave band. May I suggest you don't watch their clips on youtube. Meh! Enjoy and seed!

Jenson Interceptor - Cosmetics [1983]

Jimmy And The Boys - Teddy Boys Picnic [1981]

Swing Set - Life Speeds Up [1986]

The Lads - Out From The Shadows [1983]
